<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41071e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41071e">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41071e"> 71(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> pressure on one</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Whether, in such a case, the two are tried separately or together is a matter enirely in the discretion of the Court before which they are brought; and if any hardship or injustice ensues to one or other of the accused persons through the weight of evidence offered against both <mark>pressing unduly against either</mark>, the only remedy lies in the Court of Appeal. <small> Filson Young, <a name="FYTF" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FYTF"><cite title="source">Trial of Frederick Bywaters and Edith Thompson</cite></a> (1923) xxi</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
